<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,901,1357]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
REMARKS: Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Herting, B. &amp; Dely-Draskovits, A." box="[403,872,1175,1201]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="118 - 458" refId="ref132252" refString="Herting, B. &amp; Dely-Draskovits, A. (1993) Family Tachinidae, pp. 118 - 458. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Volume 13. Anthomyiidae - Tachinidae. Hungarian Natural History Museum, Budapest. 624 pp. [15 December] [Dated from Evenhuis (2008 b).]" type="book chapter" year="1993">Herting &amp; Dely-Draskovits (1993: 427)</bibRefCitation>
gave the method of 
<typeStatus box="[1117,1167,1175,1201]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">type</typeStatus>
fixation for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[1317,1436,1175,1200]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Exogaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1317,1436,1175,1200]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Exogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[277,507,1214,1240]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="10" refId="ref144790" refString="Rondani, C. (1856) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: I. Genera italica ordinis dipterorum ordinatim disposita et distincta et in familias et stirpes aggregata. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma]. 226 + [2] pp. [10 September] [Dated from advertisement from publisher in Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung.]" type="journal article" year="1856">Rondani (1856: 78)</bibRefCitation>
as by original designation, they listed the 
<typeStatus box="[1008,1058,1214,1240]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">type</typeStatus>
species as dating from 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="268 - 277" refId="ref145311" refString="Rondani, C. (1861 c) Ocypterae italicae observatae et distinctae. Comentarium XIX pro dipterologia italica. Archivio per la Zoologia, l'Anatomia e la Fisiologia, 1, 268 - 277, 282, pl. XI A - B. [31 December +] [This and the following article were printed on successive pages with the legend for the plate for this article appearing at the end of the article below (on page 282).]" type="journal article" year="1861">Rondani (1861c: 277</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[450,586,1253,1279]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref145440" refString="Rondani, C. (1861 e) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol. IV. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analatica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars tertia: Muscidae, Tachininarum complementum. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma]. 174 pp. [31 December +] [For dating, see Sabrosky (1961) and Evenhuis (1997: 662).]" type="book" year="1861">1861e: 131</bibRefCitation>
). This is incorrect. The characters in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[1033,1265,1253,1279]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="10" refId="ref144790" refString="Rondani, C. (1856) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: I. Genera italica ordinis dipterorum ordinatim disposita et distincta et in familias et stirpes aggregata. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma]. 226 + [2] pp. [10 September] [Dated from advertisement from publisher in Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung.]" type="journal article" year="1856">Rondani (1856: 78)</bibRefCitation>
that make the genus-group name available serve to also make available 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[931,1169,1292,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Exogaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis box="[931,1169,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Exogaster carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the singly included species.
</paragraph>
